  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to determine whether heated humidified high flow nasal cannula
      (HHHFNC) is effective as a treatment of obstructive sleep apnea syndrome (OSAS) compared to
      continues positive airway pressure (CPAP) treatments in children and to compare their
      adherence and compliance.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
